<body>

    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">1. How does EaseCook work?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>EaseCook uses AI to analyze photos of your ingredients and generates personalized recipes based on what you have on hand.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">2. What types of recipes can I expect?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>You can expect a wide variety of recipes, from quick snacks to full meals, tailored to your available ingredients.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">3. Can I specify dietary preferences?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>Yes! EaseCook allows you to choose dietary preferences, including healthy options, filling meals, or lower-calorie dishes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">4. Do I need an account to use EaseCook?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>No account is necessary for basic use, but creating an account allows you to save your favorite recipes and preferences.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">5. Is EaseCook free to use?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>Yes, EaseCook is free to use, with optional premium features available for advanced recipe customization.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h2 class="question">6. How can I contact support?</h2>
        <div class="answer">
            <p>You can reach our support team via the contact form on our website or by emailing support@easecook.com.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const questions = document.querySelectorAll('.question');
        questions.forEach(question => {
            question.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const answer = question.nextElementSibling;
                answer.classList.toggle('open');

                // Adjust height for smoother animation
                if (answer.classList.contains('open')) {
                    answer.style.height = `${answer.scrollHeight}px`;
                } else {
                    answer.style.height = '0';
                }
            });
        });
    </script>

